{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/agile-scrum-notes-07/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"zehengl","author":"Zeheng Li","siteUrl":"https://zehengl.github.io"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"b3d5473f-a4de-5d6c-a14c-ecf95a92edc8","excerpt":"Principles behind Agile planning Planning in Agile is considered as a “Speculative” activity, i.e., you make a forecast that is reasonable, based on the…","fields":{"readingTime":{"text":"4 min read"}},"html":"<h2>Principles behind Agile planning</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Planning in Agile is considered as a “Speculative” activity, i.e., you make a forecast that is reasonable, based on the available information</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>The plan is elaborated and becomes more and more definitive over a period of time</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Normally on Agile projects, you plan based on “time-boxes”, i.e., fix the time and resources available and determine the features that can be delivered</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>The plan has to be flexible and planning is an on-going activity</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Try not to pack too much into the plan - allow space to accommodate changes</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Iterations allow for mid-course corrections</h2>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/01e61f957ccf747a55ee7c732c690868/8608d/iterations-allow-for-mid-course-corrections.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 54.05405405405405%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"iterations-allow-for-mid-course-corrections\"\n        title=\"iterations-allow-for-mid-course-corrections\"\n        src=\"/static/01e61f957ccf747a55ee7c732c690868/1c72d/iterations-allow-for-mid-course-corrections.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/01e61f957ccf747a55ee7c732c690868/a80bd/iterations-allow-for-mid-course-corrections.jpg 148w,\n/static/01e61f957ccf747a55ee7c732c690868/1c91a/iterations-allow-for-mid-course-corrections.jpg 295w,\n/static/01e61f957ccf747a55ee7c732c690868/1c72d/iterations-allow-for-mid-course-corrections.jpg 590w,\n/static/01e61f957ccf747a55ee7c732c690868/8608d/iterations-allow-for-mid-course-corrections.jpg 638w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h2>Multiple levels of planning</h2>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 500px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/a04785fda9baf49a2a5293c635cf7bf3/0b533/planning-onion.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 69.5945945945946%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"planning-onion\"\n        title=\"planning-onion\"\n        src=\"/static/a04785fda9baf49a2a5293c635cf7bf3/0b533/planning-onion.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/a04785fda9baf49a2a5293c635cf7bf3/12f09/planning-onion.png 148w,\n/static/a04785fda9baf49a2a5293c635cf7bf3/e4a3f/planning-onion.png 295w,\n/static/a04785fda9baf49a2a5293c635cf7bf3/0b533/planning-onion.png 500w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Iteration planning considers the tasks that are needed to transform a <strong>Feature Request</strong> into working, tested software</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Iteration Planning occurs at the start of each iteration</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Product Planning involves a product owner looking ahead than the immediate release and planning for the evolution of released system</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Portfolio planning involves the selection of the products that will best implement a vision established through an organization’s strategic planning</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Release planning</h2>\n<p>A Release Plan presents a roadmap of how the team intends to achieve the product vision within the project objectives and constraints identified up-front</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>It helps the product owner and the whole team decide how much must be developed and how long that will take before they have a releasable product</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>A release conveys expectations about what is likely to be developed and in what timeframe</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>A release plan serves as a guidepost toward which the project team can progress</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Steps to planning a release</h2>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/fd27399ea26b6fdca788107d8c00594f/f0b2f/steps-in-release-planning.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 33.108108108108105%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"steps-to-planning-a-release\"\n        title=\"steps-to-planning-a-release\"\n        src=\"/static/fd27399ea26b6fdca788107d8c00594f/1c72d/steps-in-release-planning.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/fd27399ea26b6fdca788107d8c00594f/a80bd/steps-in-release-planning.jpg 148w,\n/static/fd27399ea26b6fdca788107d8c00594f/1c91a/steps-in-release-planning.jpg 295w,\n/static/fd27399ea26b6fdca788107d8c00594f/1c72d/steps-in-release-planning.jpg 590w,\n/static/fd27399ea26b6fdca788107d8c00594f/a8a14/steps-in-release-planning.jpg 885w,\n/static/fd27399ea26b6fdca788107d8c00594f/f0b2f/steps-in-release-planning.jpg 1078w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>The team and product owner collaboratively explore the product owner’s conditions of satisfaction that include scope, schedule, budget, and quality.</p>\n<h2>Release Planning</h2>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 424px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/7f309196a2420984755ef1413d0772eb/4e76e/revised-release-plan.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 54.05405405405405%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"release-planning-meeting\"\n        title=\"release-planning-meeting\"\n        src=\"/static/7f309196a2420984755ef1413d0772eb/4e76e/revised-release-plan.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/7f309196a2420984755ef1413d0772eb/a80bd/revised-release-plan.jpg 148w,\n/static/7f309196a2420984755ef1413d0772eb/1c91a/revised-release-plan.jpg 295w,\n/static/7f309196a2420984755ef1413d0772eb/4e76e/revised-release-plan.jpg 424w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 424px) 100vw, 424px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>The purpose of Release Planning is to define the contents of a release or a specific shippable product increment.</p>\n<h2>Velocity</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Velocity is a measure of a team’s rate of progress per Sprint</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>It is calculated by summing the number of story points assigned to each user story that the team <strong>completed</strong> during the Sprint.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Sprint planning</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>The Goal of Sprint planning is for the team to make a “good commitment” about what they will deliver at the end of the Sprint</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>A “good commitment” means:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Everybody is clear about the goals</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Everybody agrees that it is “achievable”</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>It should be achievable without sacrificing:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Sustainable pace</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Quality (near releasable quality)</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>A Sprint pre-planning meeting and preparations would help</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Velocity driven sprint planning</h2>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 309px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/bb7babde65bc8c06c0da8b3113d8d5ef/532e8/velocity-driven-sprint-planning.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 143.24324324324326%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"velocity-driven-sprint-planning\"\n        title=\"velocity-driven-sprint-planning\"\n        src=\"/static/bb7babde65bc8c06c0da8b3113d8d5ef/532e8/velocity-driven-sprint-planning.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/bb7babde65bc8c06c0da8b3113d8d5ef/12f09/velocity-driven-sprint-planning.png 148w,\n/static/bb7babde65bc8c06c0da8b3113d8d5ef/e4a3f/velocity-driven-sprint-planning.png 295w,\n/static/bb7babde65bc8c06c0da8b3113d8d5ef/532e8/velocity-driven-sprint-planning.png 309w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 309px) 100vw, 309px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h2>Commitment driven sprint planning</h2>\n<p><img src=\"/d67c2848b8e68764bc6d11441f5db977/commitment-driven-sprint-planning.gif\" alt=\"commitment-driven-sprint-planning\"></p>\n<p>In Commitment driven sprint planning, the team is asked to add stories to the sprint one-by-one until they can commit to completing no more.</p>\n<h2>Find out how much time is available</h2>\n<p>Allow time for:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Hacking, reading blogs, 20% time?</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Lunch, tea breaks</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Email</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Meetings</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Fixing P1 bugs from previous version</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Time committed to other teams</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Planning for each story</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Find out what “tasks” are needed</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Design / Design review</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Code</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Unit test</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>System and regression test</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Documentation</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Bug fixing</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Assign tasks to resources and re-estimate the tasks</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Make sure the team member has time available</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Keep in mind before finalizing the plan</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Does everybody in the team have enough (not too little and not too much) work to do?</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Have you considered correct capacity (e.g. account for planned leaves)?</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Do you have some buffer to accommodate unplanned absence or other contingencies?</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Have you kept time aside for Scrum rituals: Planning, Stand-ups, Review, Retrospective?</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Do you understand the dependencies and have they been tied up?</p>\n</li>\n</ul>","frontmatter":{"title":"Agile Scrum Note 07: Planning","date":"2016-01-23","description":"Information about Scrum planning."}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/agile-scrum-notes-07/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/simple-web-scraper/"},"frontmatter":{"tags":["python"],"title":"Simple Web Scraper"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/agile-scrum-notes-08/"},"frontmatter":{"tags":["agile","scrum"],"title":"Agile Scrum Note 08: Estimation"}}}},"staticQueryHashes":["4157253893","63159454"]}